       <h1>WHEAT</h1>
       <div class="overlay">
        <i class="ri-arrow-right-line"></i>
        <h4>WHEAT</h4>
        <p>Seasons: Wheat is typically planted in the fall for winter wheat or in the spring for spring wheat. <br><br>
          Soil: It thrives in well-drained, loamy soils that are rich in organic matter and nitrogen. <br><br>
          Irrigation Techniques: Common methods include flood irrigation, furrow irrigation, drip irrigation, and sprinklers, tailored to water availability and efficiency.

          </p> 
</div>
   </div>
   <div class="box1" id="b">
    <h1>PADDY</h1>
    <div class="overlay">
      <i class="ri-arrow-right-line"></i>
      <h4>PADDY</h4>
      <p>Seasons: Paddy is usually planted in the wet or rainy season, depending on the variety and region. <br><br>
       
     Soil: It prefers flooded or waterlogged fields, particularly in clayey or loamy soils. <br><br>
     Irrigation Techniques: Paddy fields are typically flooded, primarily through flood irrigation. Water-saving techniques like alternate wetting and drying (AWD) are gaining popularity, where fields are allowed to partially dry between floodings.
        </p>
</div>
  </div>
<div class="box1" id="c">
  <h1>LENTILS</h1>
  <div class="overlay">
    <i class="ri-arrow-right-line"></i>
    <h4>LENTILS</h4>
    <p>Seasons: Lentils are typically grown in cool-season climates. They are sown in late winter to early spring or late summer to early autumn, depending on the region and variety.
<br><br>
      Soil: Lentils thrive in well-drained sandy or loamy soils with good organic matter content. They prefer slightly acidic to neutral pH levels.
      <br><br>
      Irrigation Techniques: Lentils generally require moderate water. Irrigation methods like furrow or drip irrigation are suitable, ensuring the soil remains consistently moist but not waterlogged during the growing season.</p>

    </div>
</div>
<div class="box1" id="d">
  <h1>SUGARCANE</h1>
  <div class="overlay">
    <i class="ri-arrow-right-line"></i>
    <h4>SUGARCANE</h4>
    <p>Seasons: Sugarcane is primarily grown in tropical and subtropical regions throughout the year.
     <br><br> Soil: It thrives in well-drained, loamy soils with plenty of organic matter and slightly acidic to neutral pH.
     <br><br> Irrigation Techniques: Sugarcane benefits from regular and ample water. Drip irrigation and furrow systems are commonly used to ensure consistent moisture levels for optimal growth and sugar yield.</p>
</div>
</div>
