  <div class="center">
   <div class="box1" id="a">
       <h1>NITROGEN (N)</h1>
       <div class="overlay">
        <i class="ri-arrow-right-line"></i>
        <h4>NITROGEN (N)</h4>
        <p>Benefits: Nitrogen is essential for wheat's vegetative growth and protein synthesis. It helps in increasing the yield and improving grain quality. <br><br>
          How to use: Apply nitrogen fertilizers in split doses. The first application can be done at planting or during the tillering stage, and additional doses can be applied during stem elongation or booting stages. The amount and timing of nitrogen application can vary depending on soil type, wheat variety, and local conditions.</p>
</div>
   </div>
   <div class="box1" id="b">
    <h1>PHOSPHROUS (P)</h1>
    <div class="overlay">
      <i class="ri-arrow-right-line"></i>
      <h4>PHOSPHOROUS (P)</h4>
      <p>
        Benefits: Phosphorus is vital for strong root development and early growth in paddy plants. It supports flowering and grain formation. <br><br>
        How to use: Apply phosphorus fertilizers during planting or as a basal application before transplanting. Incorporate it into the soil for better root access</p>
</div>
  </div>
<div class="box1" id="c">
  <h1>POTASSIUM (K)</h1>
  <div class="overlay">
    <i class="ri-arrow-right-line"></i>
    <h4>POTASSIUM (K)</h4><p>Benefits: Potassium helps with lentil plant vigor, disease resistance, and overall plant health. It can enhance yield and quality. <br><br>
      How to use: Apply potassium fertilizers during early growth stages and pod development. Top-dressing may be necessary if your soil is deficient in potassium.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="box1" id="d">
  <h1>MICRONUTRIENT</h1>
  <div class="overlay">
    <i class="ri-arrow-right-line"></i>
    <h4>MICRONUTRIENT</h4>
    <p>
      In some cases, lentils may require micronutrients like boron, zinc, and iron. Soil tests or plant tissue analysis can help diagnose deficiencies. <br><br>
      Application rates and methods for micronutrient fertilizers depend on specific deficiency findings.</p>
</div>
</div>
