<div class="page4">
  <div class="up">
   <h4>DISEASES IN CROPS</h4>
   <h4>DIAGNOSIS OF DISEASES</h4>
  </div>
  <div class="center">
   <div class="box1" id="a">
       <h1>LEAF RUST</h1>
       <div class="overlay">
        <i class="ri-arrow-right-line"></i>
        <h4>LEAF RUST</h4>
        <p>Symptoms: Small, reddish-brown pustules on the leaves that can merge and cause severe damage. <br><br>
          Diagnosis: Visual inspection of leaves. <br><br>
          Cure: Fungicides can be applied during the growing season to manage leaf rust. Choosing rust-resistant wheat varieties is also an effective preventive measure.</p>
</div>
   </div>
   <div class="box1" id="b">
    <h1>SCAB</h1>
    <div class="overlay">
      <i class="ri-arrow-right-line"></i>
      <h4>SCAB</h4>
      <p>Symptoms: Scabby, shriveled grains and infected heads. <br><br>
        Diagnosis: Inspection of the wheat heads. <br><br>
        Cure: Fungicides can be used, but they are more effective for prevention if applied before flowering. Crop rotation with non-host crops can help reduce disease pressure.</p>
</div>
  </div>
<div class="box1" id="c">
  <h1>LEAF BLOTCH</h1>
  <div class="overlay">
    <i class="ri-arrow-right-line"></i>
    <h4>LEAF BLOTCH</h4>
    <p>Symptoms: Dark, necrotic spots with yellow margins on the leaves. <br><br>
      Diagnosis: Visual inspection of leaves. <br><br>
      Cure: Fungicides can be used when the disease is severe. Crop rotation and selecting resistant varieties can help prevent it.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="box1" id="d">
  <h1>STEM RUST</h1>
  <div class="overlay">
    <i class="ri-arrow-right-line"></i>
    <h4>STEM RUST</h4>
    <p>Symptoms: Brown pustules on the stems. <br><br>
      Diagnosis: Visual inspection of stems. <br><br>
      Cure: Fungicides can be applied, but planting rust-resistant varieties is a more effective strategy.</p>
</div>
